Thomas Jordan Driver, 25, David Elliot Moran, 47, and Charles Thomas Newcomb, 42, were arrested Thursday on one state count of conspiracy to commit murder, Florida Attorney General Pam Bondi's office said .
The three men worked at the Department of Corrections Reception and Medical Center in rural north Florida .
Driver, an officer at the facility, was fired in 2013 for failing to meet training requirements, according to an arrest affidavit .